dden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tza1665702561698.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tza1665702561698.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tza1665702561698.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tza1665702561698\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n    Modeled Entity </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Modeled Entity is an Entity that defines a logical data aggregation at an abstract\n    level. It is used to model the default properties and code of an entity, so that the Entity can\n    be referenced and inherited by derived entities in components. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tza1665702561698__section_s4c_xsp_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d229060e51\">Characteristics</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Characteristics</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__2\"></th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Icon:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\"><img alt=\"Icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"tza1665702561698__image_f3l_ntp_lwb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/entity.png?_LANG=enus\"/></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Object type code:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">ent</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Main Development Object?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Part of:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Contains:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zhd1665702557352.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zhd1665702557352.html\" title=\"A Modeled Field is a Development Object that represents a unit of data in a Modeled Entity.\">Modeled Field</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vuv1665702701508.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vuv1665702701508.html\" title=\"A Key is a Development Object that designates a field or combination of fields as a Primary Key, Candidate Key, or Index.\">Key</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xtb1665702702029.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xtb1665702702029.html\" title=\"A Relationship is a Development Object that represents an association between one entity and another. It specifies the primary or candidate keys to be used in maintaining the association, as well as the delete constraints to be used when deleting occurrences in the related entities.\">Relationship</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jgi1665702550212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jgi1665702550212.html\" title=\"A Property is a named, typed attribute of Development Object that defines a characteristic or behavior of the object. Each property has a descriptive name, a literal name, a data type, and a value. If no value is specified, a default value may be used.\">Property</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cny1665702550298.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cny1665702550298.html\" title=\"A Code Container is a type of Property that holds code, such as ProcScript, JavaScript, or HTML. It can contain one or more code modules, such as triggers, operations, functions, or entries, or HTML for the layout.\">Code Container</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Generalizations:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uqv1665702561461.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uqv1665702561461.html\" title=\"An Entity is an abstract data type that defines a logical data aggregation and its associated default characteristics and behavior. It may be mapped to a table in a DBMS, and is most frequently used to represent the application data, but it can also represent transient data, a collection of controls, or constant data.\">Entity</a> , <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"srw1665702550375.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/srw1665702550375.html\" title=\"A Main Development Object is a Development Object that has no parent object, is maintained using a dedicated editor, and can be saved and exported as a single unit, with all its children.\">Main Development Object</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specializations:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mmw1665703024582.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mmw1665703024582.html\" title=\"A Supertype Entity is an Entity that has one or more Subtype Entities.\">Supertype Entity</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cnq1665702702174.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cnq1665702702174.html\" title=\"A Subtype Entity specializes a Modeled Entity (also known as the Supertype Entity). It is used to define a data set (or subset) for a special purpose, but that can be stored in the same database table as its Supertype.\">Subtype Entity</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Compilation Output:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityName</var>.edc</span>, Entity Collection Signature,\n                  Occurrence Collection Signature, SQL scripts</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">URI format:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tza1665702561698__table_d10478e1_d10479e1_d10480e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ent:<var class=\"keyword varname\">EntityName.ModelName</var>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tza1665702561698__section_sch_vsp_lwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d229060e311\">Specialization</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tza1665702561698__p_d94736e1_d94737e1_d94738e1\">\n<dfn class=\"term\">Modeled Entity</dfn> specializes <dfn class=\"term\">Main Development Object</dfn> and\n          <dfn class=\"term\">Entity</dfn> in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"tza1665702561698__ul_cnp_5tp_lwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tza1665702561698__li_d37112e1_d37113e1_d37114e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tza1665702561698__p_d94739e1_d94740e1_d94741e1\">It has no parent.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tza1665702561698__li_d37115e1_d37116e1_d37117e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tza1665702561698__p_d94742e1_d94743e1_d94744e1\">It can contain modeled fields, keys, and\n            relationships.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tza1665702561698__li_d37118e1_d37119e1_d37120e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tza1665702561698__p_d94745e1_d94746e1_d94747e1\">It must have a primary key.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616235\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616235\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Modeled Entity Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Modeled Entity A Modeled Entity is an Entity that defines a logical data aggregation at an abstract level. It is used to model the default properties and code of an entity, so that the Entity can be referenced and inherited by derived entities in components. Characteristics Characteristics Icon: Object type code: ent Main Development Object? Yes Part of: — Contains: Modeled Field , Key , Relationship , Property , Code Container Generalizations: Entity , Main Development Object Specializations: Supertype Entity , Subtype Entity Compilation Output: EntityName .edc , Entity Collection Signature, Occurrence Collection Signature, SQL scripts URI format: ent: EntityName.ModelName Specialization Modeled Entity specializes Main Development Object and Entity in the following ways: It has no parent. It can contain modeled fields, keys, and relationships. It must have a primary key. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}